## 10. Exploitation — Wireless

- **WEP** — fundamentally broken, crackable via IV collection (`aircrack-ng` suite) — rarely seen anymore but good to know why it failed (weak IV reuse).
- **WPA2/WPA3** — handshake capture + offline cracking (WPA2-PSK), KRACK attack (WPA2 protocol flaw), Dragonblood (WPA3 side-channel flaws).
- **Rogue access points / evil twin attacks** — impersonating a legitimate SSID to capture credentials.
- **Enterprise wireless (802.1X)** — attacking RADIUS misconfigurations, certificate validation bypass.
- Tools: `aircrack-ng`, `Kismet`, `Wifite`, `hashcat` (for handshake cracking).

