## 11. Social Engineering & Physical Security Testing

- **Phishing** — credential harvesting pages, payload delivery, pretexting based on OSINT-gathered employee/organizational detail.
- **Vishing** (voice phishing) and **smishing** (SMS phishing) — increasingly common, tested where in scope.
- **Physical assessments** — tailgating, badge cloning (RFID readers), lock bypass, dumpster diving for sensitive discarded material, USB drop attacks (leaving malicious USB drives for employees to plug in).
- **Framework tools:** Gophish (phishing campaign management), Social-Engineer Toolkit (SET).
- **Ethical/legal note:** social engineering and physical testing carry the highest risk of unintended consequences (real employee distress, law enforcement being called on a physical tester) — ROE must be extremely explicit here, including a physical "authorization letter" testers can present if challenged on-site.

